- your site, and itâ€™s content, should still be accessible when JavaScript is unavailable
- http://blog.teamtreehouse.com/beginners-guide-to-jquery
- jQuery(el) or $(el)
- .hide()
- .show()
- keep in mind method chaining is best practice for an element that is already selected
- in the console:
- document.head.children // returns an array of the head elements
- document.body.children[0] // return the first child in the body
- the above is not an ideal way to access elements that could change
- document.getElementByClassName("class")
- DOM manipulation Methods: add/remove html elements, update/ read html element attributes, and Transform HTML elements
- Traversing the DOM: Moving from a parent element to its children, moving from a child element to its parent, moving from a sibling element to another sibling element
- Event Methods: keyboard, mouse, touch, and scroll events
- Attribute Methods: get or modify the attributes of an element
- $(document).ready(function() { });
- $(function() { }); // alternate

